======================================================================
PART 3: The Phase arg(λ)/π = 1/2 + 1/(π√p) Proof
======================================================================

PROOF of arg(λ)/π = 1/2 + 1/(π√p) + O(1/p^{3/2}):

  λ = (-1 + i√p)/2 for Paley QR eigenvalues
  arg(λ) = π - arctan(√p)
  arctan(√p) = π/2 - 1/√p + 1/(3p^{3/2}) - ...
  So arg(λ)/π = 1 - (1/2 - 1/(π√p) + ...) = 1/2 + 1/(π√p) + O(1/p^{3/2})

  The 1/π coefficient arises because:
  arctan(x) ≈ π/2 - 1/x for large x
  So 1/(π√p) = (1/π) × 1/√p
  π appears because arctan is the INVERSE of tangent,
  and tan(π/2) = ∞ — we're expanding near the pole!

